- 2.0.1 | Feb 14 2026:
[New] valid_host() and valid_ip_cidr() input validation functions for trust
      system operations
[New] ipt()/ipt4()/ipt6() dual-stack iptables helper functions; ipt() runs
      both IPv4 and IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1, ipt4()/ipt6() for protocol-specific
[New] IPv6 kernel module loading when USE_IPV6=1; ip6_tables, ip6table_filter,
      nf_conntrack_ipv6
[New] nft backend detection; iptables-save snapshot includes backend marker
      (.apf.restore.backend) for safe restore across nft/legacy iptables
[Fix] RAB_PSCAN_LEVEL always-true condition; || changed to && (firewall)
[Fix] EG_DROP_CMD dead code; comparison to "1" changed to non-empty check
      (cports.common)
[Fix] missing $ prefix on LOG_DROP variable reference (cports.common)
[Fix] RESV_DNS_DROP duplicate ACCEPT rules removed from DNS filtering loop
      (firewall)
[Fix] fastload message incorrectly stated "1h" when threshold is 12h (apf)
[Fix] ovars() broken AWK expression rewritten with ${!var} indirect expansion
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] duplicate IPFLOW variable checks corrected to PFLOW in trust parsing
      x6 (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust() now validates HOST input via valid_host() before trust
      operations (functions.apf)
[Fix] sed delimiter hardened to % in cli_trust_remove() and expirebans() to
      prevent metacharacter injection (functions.apf)
[Fix] blocklist integrity validation added via valid_ip_cidr() in all dlist_*
      download functions (functions.apf)
[Fix] unquoted variable expansion in file operations (install.sh, functions.apf)
[Fix] hardcoded /sbin/ip replaced with $ip variable for cross-OS compatibility;
      breaks on RHEL 8+/Ubuntu 20+ where ip is at /usr/sbin/ip (firewall,
      vnetgen)
[Fix] hardcoded /sbin/iptables-save replaced with $IPTS variable
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] 35+ hardcoded /etc/apf/ paths replaced with $INSTALL_PATH across
      download functions, expirebans(), refresh(), cron, temp files, trust
      md5 (functions.apf, apf)
[Fix] all 8 $IP6T calls now include $IPT_FLAGS lock flag; previously skipped
      -w timeout causing potential concurrent modification (functions.apf,
      firewall, bt.rules)
[Fix] IPv6 loopback rules corrected from 0/0 to ::/0 (firewall)
[Fix] SYSCTL_TCP_NOSACK non-empty test corrected to == "1"; setting to "0"
      previously still disabled SACK (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] tcp_tw_recycle guarded behind /proc file existence; removed in kernel
      4.12 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] 4 duplicate sysctl writes removed: log_martians x2, rp_filter x2,
      accept_source_route x2 (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] conf.apf date typo "2109" corrected to "2019"
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() now validates input via valid_host() (functions.apf)
[Fix] valid_host() IPv6 regex tightened to require colon-separated groups;
      previously accepted invalid strings like "ff" or "::::" (functions.apf)
[Fix] dead variables removed: LSTOP, LACCEPT, TOS_DEF_TOS, DSTOP
      (internals.conf)
[Fix] unused MOD assignment removed from ml() function (functions.apf)
[Fix] duplicate cron.daily conditional collapsed in install.sh
[Fix] $ip usage guarded behind -n check to prevent errors when ip binary
      is absent (internals.conf)
[Fix] vnetgen ifconfig fallback uses interface line detection instead of
      grep Link which fails on modern net-tools (vnetgen)
[Fix] deprecated $[...] arithmetic replaced with $((...)) across all files
[Fix] ipchains check guarded behind kernel 2.4 detection (functions.apf)
[Fix] --cmd-owner runtime detection with graceful skip for kernels that
      removed xt_owner cmd support (cports.common)
[Change] module loading rewritten with modprobe --dry-run for portable
         detection across .ko, .ko.xz, .ko.zst extensions (functions.apf)
[Change] ip route used as primary with route as fallback for interface
         validation (firewall)
[Change] ifconfig made optional; ip command used as primary in VNET
         subsystem (vnetgen, main.vnet)
[Change] which lsmod/rmmod no longer passes redundant absolute paths
         (internals.conf)
[New] ipt()/ipt4()/ipt6() helpers adopted across rule files; protocol-agnostic
      rules now apply to both IPv4 and IPv6 when USE_IPV6=1 (firewall, bt.rules,
      log.rules, functions.apf)
[Change] chain creation, MSS clamping, connection state, default policies,
         helpers (FTP/SSH/Traceroute), logging, P2P, and IDENT rules now use
         ipt() for dual-stack support (firewall, bt.rules, log.rules)
[Change] common drop ports (cdports) now use ipt() for dual-stack blocking
         (functions.apf)
[Change] flush() refactored: default policies use ipt(), table flush loops
         use ipt4/ipt6 with separate proc chain lists (functions.apf)
[Change] cports.common port rules converted to ipt4() with redundant -s 0/0
         removed; true dual-stack port filtering deferred to Phase 10
         (cports.common)
[Change] packet sanity, fragment, multicast, lgate_mac rules converted to
         explicit ipt4() to clarify IPv4-specific intent (bt.rules,
         functions.apf)
[Change] BLK_TCP_SACK_PANIC collapsed from separate $IPT/$IP6T blocks to
         single ipt() call (bt.rules)
[Change] EG_DROP_CMD section converted to ipt4(); redundant -s 0/0 -d 0/0
         removed (cports.common)
[New] IPv6 local address detection; .localaddrs6 generated alongside
      .localaddrs when USE_IPV6=1 (firewall)
[New] IPv6 PROHIBIT chain with icmp6-adm-prohibited reject target (firewall)
[New] ipt_dst()/ipt_src() VNET-aware dual-stack helpers for port filtering;
      IPv4 gets -d/-s $VNET, IPv6 applies without address restriction
      (functions.apf)
[New] ICMPv6 filtering support with IG_ICMPV6_TYPES and EG_ICMPV6_TYPES
      config variables; NDP types 133-136 always permitted (cports.common,
      conf.apf)
[New] IPv6 DNS filtering; nameservers from resolv.conf routed to ipt4/ipt6
      based on address type (firewall)
[Change] trusted interface rules converted to ipt() dual-stack; redundant
         -s 0/0 -d 0/0 removed (firewall)
[Change] TCP/UDP port filtering converted from ipt4 to ipt_dst/ipt_src for
         dual-stack support; IPv6 gets port rules when USE_IPV6=1 (cports.common)
[Change] RESV_DNS_DROP rules converted to ipt4/ipt6 with IPv6 coverage when
         USE_IPV6=1 (firewall)
[Change] cl_cports() clears ICMPv6 variables between VNET iterations
         (functions.apf)
[Fix] SYSCTL_ROUTE else branch removed; previously ENABLED ip_forward,
      bootp_relay, and forwarding when routing protection was off, turning
      server into a router (sysctl.rules)
[Fix] allow_hosts() and deny_hosts() now validate plain IP entries via
      valid_host() before passing to iptables; prevents injection from
      malicious trust file entries (functions.apf)
[Fix] cli_trust_remove() sed pattern anchored with ^ and \b to prevent
      substring matching; 10.0.0.1 no longer removes 10.0.0.10
      (functions.apf)
[Fix] EG_DROP_CMD LOG rule now includes --cmd-owner filter; previously
      logged ALL packets in DEG chain instead of only matched commands
      (cports.common)
[Change] temp directories in download functions use mktemp -d for atomic
         creation; eliminates PID-based predictable paths and TOCTOU race
         (functions.apf)
[Change] DLIST download URLs updated from HTTP to HTTPS for all upstream
         sources: cdn.rfxn.com, spamhaus.org, feeds.dshield.org (conf.apf,
         .ca.def)
